          <zone h='74480' id='12' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='71816' x='27892' y='25000'>
            <zone h='71616' id='105' name='Top Recycled Material Group' w='70206' x='28697' y='26432'>
              <layout-cache minwidth='222' type-h='fixed' type-w='scalable' />
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#c0c0c0' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
              <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='5' />
              <format attr='margin' value='5' />
              <format attr='padding' value='5' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone h='74480' id='103' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='27600' x='292' y='25000'>
            <zone forceUpdate='true' h='50261' id='104' type-v2='text' w='25990' x='1097' y='26432'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10' underline='true'>What this Dashboard is about</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Before looking at any single material, it&apos;s worth seeing the size of what we&apos;re dealing with. England&apos;s local authorities report waste through hundreds of thousands of individual records every year, processed across well over a thousand distinct facilities nationwide — a far larger, more distributed system than most people picture when they think about &apos;recycling.&apos; The recycling rate itself has moved +0.35% between 2023 and 2025 — the first sign that this system isn&apos;t static.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#c0c0c0' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
              <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='5' />
              <format attr='margin' value='5' />
              <format attr='padding' value='5' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='2' />
            <format attr='padding' value='2' />
            <format attr='background-color' value='#e6e6e6' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='28125' id='108' type-v2='text' w='37994' x='55930' y='41406'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>Organic waste — garden and food waste — dominates by a wide margin, </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>followed by Incinerator Bottom Ash, Paper &amp; Card, and Glass. This isn&apos;t surprising once you think about it: these are the materials generated in the largest physical volumes by every household, every week. But volume alone doesn&apos;t tell the whole story — a tonne of inert glass poses very little environmental risk even in large quantities, while a much smaller tonnage of batteries, paint, or oil can cause serious harm if mishandled, despite barely registering on a tonnage chart. Volume tells you what&apos;s biggest; it doesn&apos;t tell you what matters most to get right — which is exactly what the next chapter explores</run>
          </formatted-text>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
            <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='2' />
            <format attr='background-color' value='#d4d4d4' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone h='8464' id='109' type-v2='text' w='33895' x='44583' y='76432'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='1' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Batteries, Paint, Oil, and Tyres each make up under 0.1% of total tonnage but carry disproportionate environmental risk if mishandled</run>
          </formatted-text>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
            <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='2' />
            <format attr='background-color' value='#d4d4d4' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
