    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Route Category Process'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='768' maxwidth='1366' minheight='768' minwidth='1366' preset-index='0' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='26' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='11700' id='25' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
            <zone forceUpdate='true' h='8836' id='28' type-v2='text' w='98390' x='805' y='1432'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='15'>How Clean Is the Recycling? (Route Mix Dashboard)</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#d4d4d4' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
              <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='5' />
              <format attr='margin' value='5' />
              <format attr='padding' value='5' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone h='88300' id='27' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='100000' x='0' y='11700'>
            <zone fixed-size='309' forceUpdate='true' h='85436' id='34' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='23207' x='805' y='13132'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Being collected as &apos;recyclable&apos; and actually being recycled are two different things — this chapter checks whether they match up. The finding: for most of the biggest materials, they do, almost entirely. Glass and Paper &amp; Card are roughly 99.9% Recycling — landfill and energy recovery account for only a handful of tonnes against well over a million. Organic waste is the one genuine exception, splitting meaningfully across Composting/Anaerobic Digestion, Recycling, and Energy Recovery — a more complex journey than most materials take. The takeaway: England&apos;s top materials aren&apos;t just being labeled as recyclable, they&apos;re mostly ending up properly processed</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone h='85436' id='29' name='Recycling Route Mix' w='75183' x='24012' y='13132'>
              <layout-cache minwidth='260' type-h='fixed' type-w='scalable' />
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#d4d4d4' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
              <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='5' />
              <format attr='margin' value='5' />
              <format attr='padding' value='5' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='0' />
            <format attr='padding' value='0' />
            <format attr='background-color' value='#e6e6e6' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='64' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='84000' id='63' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='84000' x='8000' y='8000'>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='8836' id='28' type-v2='text' w='98390' x='805' y='1432'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='15'>How Clean Is the Recycling? (Route Mix Dashboard)</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone fixed-size='309' forceUpdate='true' h='85436' id='34' type-v2='text' w='23207' x='805' y='13132'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Being collected as &apos;recyclable&apos; and actually being recycled are two different things — this chapter checks whether they match up. The finding: for most of the biggest materials, they do, almost entirely. Glass and Paper &amp; Card are roughly 99.9% Recycling — landfill and energy recovery account for only a handful of tonnes against well over a million. Organic waste is the one genuine exception, splitting meaningfully across Composting/Anaerobic Digestion, Recycling, and Energy Recovery — a more complex journey than most materials take. The takeaway: England&apos;s top materials aren&apos;t just being labeled as recyclable, they&apos;re mostly ending up properly processed</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
